title: First Things First Manifesto 1964 ... What is this typeface?
content:
Hello!

I am wondering what the typeface is that is used in the 1967 ’First Things First’ manifesto... for the ’first things first part.

Can anyone help?

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20081006194943im_/http:/typophile.com/files/Picture%207_6223.png)

 [‹ modern serif font?](http://web.archive.org/web/20081006194943/http:/typophile.com/node/50193 "Go to previous forum topic") [Help IDing 50's font ›](http://web.archive.org/web/20081006194943/http:/typophile.com/node/50209 "Go to next forum topic")
author: Fushia

comments.content: It looks hand drawn to me.

This looks very similar to British Inserat. The letter ’t’ is violently different but just have a look at the link below

[http://www.linotype.com/310746/britishinserat-font.html](http://web.archive.org/web/20081006194943/http:/www.linotype.com/310746/britishinserat-font.html "http://www.linotype.com/310746/britishinserat-font.html")

Hope it helps! Cheers!
